        <h2>HTML:</h2>
        <h4>Date: 2-SEPT-2023:</h4>
        <p>Absolute Links - Any link that gies to HTTPS:// will go to an external link.</p>
        <p>Relative Links - Are any links that you are linking within your website, these could be links
            to image files or seperate files that you are calling in from a folder.</p>
        <p>Starting an HTML file, the sequence looks like:</p>
        <p>&lt;html&gt;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;head&gt;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;title&gt;Title&lt;&sol;title&gt;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;&sol;head&gt;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;body&gt;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Add your content in here, h1's, h2's, tables, etc.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;&sol;body&gt;</p>
        <p>&lt;&sol;html&gt;</p>
        <p>I also used HTML Entities which helped me to display the brakcets and forward slashes necessary as per above diagram.</p>
        <p>Here is a link to the <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_symbols.asp">W3 Schools Entities</a></p>
        <p>I used tables, table rows and table data fields, this is something that I will be just automising going forward.
            However I know how to use the Table Head, the Table, Table Rows and Table Data.
        </p>
